cs.SE, cs.RO, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of industrial automation systems using a system-based approach and a framework to refine the UML model of the software part. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of PLCs and embedded boards in the development of IASs, which are commonly used in robotics. 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of embedded boards in the implementation of IASs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the development of cyber-physical systems and their interfaces. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of the IEC 61131 standard and Java for the implementation of IASs.
